                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16823422" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2019 20:19:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can confirm the issue but it is limited to high dpi values. It works fine e.g. for 300 dpi. It seems to be a JDK/JRE issue but I didn&apos;t dig deeper into it to be sure&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16823449" author="tilman" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2019 20:46:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same with jdk11 and 12 at 1000% (image size: 67410 x 47680) in PDFDebugger.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16823736" author="tilman" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2019 06:30:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I didn&apos;t get a stack trace but by debugging I found that it happens in createPackedRaster, w * h brings a negative number as a result, because 3_214_108_800 is larger than the largest signed integer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16824849" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2019 06:38:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about implementing a max value check: w * h &amp;lt; Integer.MAX_VALUE ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16824856" author="tilman" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2019 06:56:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes. Throw an IOException when bigger?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16825162" author="eduardo quintanilla" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2019 13:49:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That would be great, as a workaround i am generating the image with ICEpdf but i am depending in a seemingly unrelated exception. Maybe a precheck method for supported file verification could be added.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sample with&#160;ICEpdf&#160;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12966894/12966894_Bottom_plate-Model.jpg&quot; title=&quot;Bottom_plate-Model.jpg attached to PDFBOX-4518&quot;&gt;Bottom_plate-Model.jpg&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16827967" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 28 Apr 2019 12:14:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1858324 from lehmi@apache.org in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1858324&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1858324&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4518&quot; title=&quot;NegativeArraySizeException thrown when converting PDF to Image&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4518&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4518&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: throw an IOException if the size (w*h) of the output image exceeds the maximum value Integer.MAX_VALUE to avoid a misleading NegativeArraySizeException&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16827968" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 28 Apr 2019 12:14:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1858325 from lehmi@apache.org in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1858325&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1858325&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4518&quot; title=&quot;NegativeArraySizeException thrown when converting PDF to Image&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4518&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4518&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: throw an IOException if the size (w*h) of the output image exceeds the maximum value Integer.MAX_VALUE to avoid a misleading NegativeArraySizeException&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16827972" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 28 Apr 2019 12:20:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve implemented the proposed check and an IOException is thrown if it fails. This won&apos;t fix the described issue but makes it clear what exactly went wrong, so that the user might adjust the scaling value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The support such high resolutions we would have to rewrite the whole renderer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Eduardo+Quintanilla&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Eduardo Quintanilla&quot;&gt;Eduardo Quintanilla&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for the report&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
